.container
  .full_width
    %h2 Everything you need to know before submitting
    .accordion
      .accord-single
        .accord-toggle
          .bold.red
            =fa_icon "plus-circle"
            Why an open call for solutions?
        .accord-cont
          .inner_container
            .half
              %p.bold.low_margin Instead of starting at zero, we want to build on existing knowledge and experience 
              %p We believe that there are people who have solved this challenge before us. Maybe in a different context, maybe with a different focus. None the less, we want to build on these experiences to leapfrog to solutions that we know have potential to make a change.
              %p.bold.low_margin Believing in the skills of others 
              %p As GIZ, we are aware that solutions to this challenge might exist somewhere, created by small or large organisations, start-ups, NGOs or private individual that might not yet be connected to us. We would like to change this by inviting them to participate in an open call for solutions.
            .half
              %p.bold.low_margin Adapting the solutions to align with needs of local communities 
              %p A jury will select the three solutions with the biggest potential, to be tested and adapted on-site to align with the needs of local communities during a design lead workshop and prototyping phase. As an example country, we chose Rwanda. However, the objective is, to scale successful solutions in other countries who combat similar challenges.
              %p.bold.low_margin Pitching to attract investors 
              %p After receiving seed funding from GIZ to develop a first MVP, local teams will pitch their solutions to attract further investment for increasing the impact through scaling.

      .accord-single
        .accord-toggle
          .bold.red
            =fa_icon "plus-circle"
            Who can participate?
        .accord-cont
          .inner_container
            .half
              %p.bold We are hoping to receive a wide range of possible solutions. In order to participate you need to:
              %p.bold.low_margin Submit a tested and implemented solution. 
              %p We don’t want to reinvent the wheel, but build on existing knowledge and experience. You can participate as an NGO, a private individual or a company – as long as your idea has been tested and implemented elsewhere.
              %p.bold.low_margin A solution that can be adapted and handed over. 
              %p The solution does not need to be rooted in Rwanda, but needs to have potential to be adapted to fit the local context. The objective is for locals to take ownership and continue adapting it.
            .half
              %p.bold.low_margin Be able to spend a week in Rwanda. 
              %p Together, we will spend one week in Rwanda, where you can share your experience with locals from host and refugee communities. We will follow a design-led approach to develop rapid prototypes and seek feedback from local users. Flight and accommodation will be payed for.

      .accord-single
        .accord-toggle
          .bold.red
            =fa_icon "plus-circle"
            What makes a good solution?
        .accord-cont
          .inner_container
            .half
              %p.bold A jury – including members from GIZ, other leading organisations and possible users - will select the three best ideas. A good idea follows these principals:
              %p.bold.low_margin Do no harm 
              %p We are aware that any interventions could lead to results that are difficult to foresee. We are looking for solutions that are responsible and respectful towards locals and avoid negative impact.
              %p.bold.low_margin Fostering financial self reliance 
              %p We are looking for solutions that help people to lead an independent life providing them with the opportunity of a regular income.
            .half
              %p.bold.low_margin Creating a benefit for refugee and host
              %p We are looking for solutions that are not only focused on supporting refugees, but also provide a benefit to members of host communities and strengthen their relationships
              %p.bold.low_margin Enabling communities 
              %p The solutions need to respond to people’s needs and work in the local context. We would love to see local people take ownership of the solutions instead of providing a service to them.
              %p.bold.low_margin Potential to scale 
              %p We picked Rwanda as an example. Similar challenges exist in other countries like Jordan, Tanzania or Iraq. We are looking for ideas that have the potential to scale, first in Rwanda than beyond.

      .accord-single
        .accord-toggle
          .bold.red
            =fa_icon "plus-circle"
            What happens to my idea and how do refugees profit?
        .accord-cont
          .inner_container
            .half
              %p.bold Your idea will be inspiration to refugee and host communities all over the world. If the prototype is successful, GIZ will support different communities to scale it globally in.
              %p.bold.low_margin Who owns the idea? 
              %p The idea is yours – of course. By sharing your knowledge and experience with host and refugee communities you will inspire them to adapt the solution to their local context.
            .half
              %p.bold.low_margin How do refugees profit? 
              %p Your experience and the support of GIZ will provide refugees and host communities an opportunity to become financially independent.



      .accord-single
        .accord-toggle
          .bold.red
            =fa_icon "plus-circle"
            If you have more questions
        .accord-cont
